# Standard-mode drag-select on the editor body produces a real
# selection. SEV-2 chrome-hunt finding (2026-06-07) was "drag-select
# moves cursor but doesn't create selection — `Sel N` indicator
# absent." This test is the regression lock.
write doc.txt "ABCDEFGHIJKLMNOPQRSTUVWXYZ"
open doc.txt
command view.toggle_tree
expect screen contains "Ln 1"

# Drag from column 10 to column 20 on screen row 2 (the first editor
# body row, since palette = row 0, bufferline = row 1). The cursor
# anchor lands at one file col, then extends 10 cells to the right,
# so the selection is exactly 10 chars wide. The original assertion
# was `Sel ` (any non-zero count) which let a SEV-2 row/col swap
# bug ship — the swap produced `Sel 94` on a 4-line file. Hard
# assertion catches that. Post-fix hunt 2026-06-08.
drag 10 2 20 2
expect screen contains "Sel 10 "
